{
  "texts": [
    "Averaging word embeddings provide a basic way to represent documents but this still lacks the capacity to fully capture the interplay among words.",
    "Transformer architectures have addressed this limitation.",
    "Introduced by Vaswani, Shazeer, Parmar, Uszkoreit, Jones, Gomez, Kaiser and Polosukhin (2017), transformers analyze the relationships between all words in a sequence simultaneously, rather than sequentially.",
    "Using a mechanism called \"attention\", they weigh the importance of each word relative to others in the text, effectively capturing context and meaning.",
    "This capability allows transformers to generate contextualized embeddings, where the meaning of each word adapts based on its context within the sentence or document."
  ]
}